Spread cream cheese on bread and cube bread. Place the cubes in a 13 x 9 baking pan, sprayed with cooking oil. Sprinkle with cinnamon, top with 1-1/2 cups of blueberries. Place sausage pieces on top of mixture in baking pan. Beat egg substitute, maple syrup and milk together. Carefully pour over mixture in baking pan. Bake in a 350 degrees F oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Top with remaining blueberries before serving.